OL,5, Football commentator Martin Tyler has  
OL,6, apologised after referring to          
OL,7, "Hillsborough and other                
OL,8, hooligan-related issues" in a BBC      
OL,9, interview.                             
OL,11,FThe Sky Sports commentator made the    
OL,12,Freference while appearing on BBC Radio 
OL,13,F4's Today programme.                   
OL,15,FLiverpool Metro Mayor Steve Rotheram   
OL,16,Finsisted Mr Tyler said sorry for his   
OL,17,F"exceptionally crass" words.           
OL,19,FMr Tyler later apologised, while the   
OL,20,FBBC said it regretted not challenging  
OL,21,Fhis remarks "robustly".                
